how do i get my wk old baby how do i get my wk old baby to sleep in her crib i know i made the mistake of letting her sleep with us and now she's getting to big we want our bed back do you think i should just let her cry it out i don't know what to do i actually started a whole bedtime routine with my son when he was that age he had a bath he nursed i sang his special night song and then i rocked him to sleep it worked like a charm sometimes babies just need extra work at getting them to wind down at the end of the day rocking or walking the house with you baby can oftentimes do the trick without having to resort to the cry it out method Phoebe Buffay's songs What Ever Happened to Baby Jane? (film) Knots Landing Sheryl Crow Lisa's First Word Love and Theft Aerial (dance move) Sleeping with the Enemy (Simpsons episode) Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Cliff Richard Frankie Laine Bringing It All Back Home Leo Wyatt Jon Secada Shaggy dog story Sudden infant death syndrome The Beatles discography Co-sleeping Johnnie Ray EastEnders Freddy Fender Odyssey Episodes of Lost (Season 1) The Rock and Roll Hall of Fame's 500 Songs that Shaped Rock and Roll Madonna (entertainer) Insomnia Donna Summer Tom Jones (singer) The Care Bears (television series) Infant The Shining (film) Remix Otello Urinary incontinence The Catcher in the Rye Characters in the Smurfs Friends Daylight saving time Sleep Treehouse of Horror XII AFI 100 Years series Sleeping Murder My Family (television) Gregg Alexander The Miracles Journey (band) Buddy Guy Bleed Like Me The Amber Spyglass Scott Storch The Flintstones The Rutles Ja Rule Bon Jovi Ayyavazhi mythology The Cure The Misfits Care Bears Breastfeeding Shrek 2 The Four Seasons (group) The SpongeBob SquarePants Movie Spandau Prison Max Martin Skateboarding trick The Reeve's Prologue and Tale One-hit wonders in the UK The Sims Night (book) Street-Legal Ray Charles Ashanti (singer) Ramones Charly Garc__a Lullaby The Star Wars Holiday Specia